While we conclude that CL is still unable to derive all effects of even (e.g. with ‘functional standards’), and thus does not seem to lie at the core of its scalar presupposition, our findings can help sketch when CL can be nonetheless safely used to capture the interpretational effects of even and when it cannot.},
