is natural to make this assumption in possible worlds semantics, but is not necessarily motivated in a more fine-grained theory of meaning. Adopting Situation Semantics, I will demonstrate that the Disjunction Puzzle disappears once it is assumed that redundancy is computed with reference to a stronger notion of entailment than presupposition satisfaction.},
